						               													<description>BERRY&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Blue. Red. Yellow. Make all Blinks one color on your turn or be the first to score 10 points and you win. This unique strategy game favors the clever and punishes the greedy.&amp;#10;Blue, Red, Yellow. This is the order the Blinks cycle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SETUP:&amp;#10;Each player starts with 3 blue Blinks in their hand. To change the color of a Blink, click it once.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAMEPLAY:&amp;#10;Players take turns placing Blinks, connecting them together into a cluster. After placing their Blink, a player clicks each adjacent Blink, advancing it to the next color.&amp;#10;Attaching to 2 or fewer neighbors&amp;#10;If there are 3 or more adjacent Blinks, the player must also click the Blink they placed.&amp;#10;Attaching to 3 or more neighbors&amp;#10;After the first 6 turns, players begin each turn not by placing a Blink from their hand, but by removing a Blink from the cluster, then placing it in a new location.&amp;#10;Not all Blinks can be legally removed from the cluster at the start of a turn. Blinks with neighbors on opposite sides are &amp;ldquo;locked,&amp;rdquo; as are Blinks that, if removed, would fracture the cluster into more than&amp;#10;2 pieces.&amp;#10;SCORING:&amp;#10;Examples of locked Blinks&amp;#10;               At the end of each turn, the active player earns points for the presence of certain shapes in a singular color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;WIN CONDITION:&amp;#10;The first player to score ten or more points is the winner. However, if a player ends their turn with all 6 Blinks set to the same color, they are the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game is played with Blinks, the world's first smart tabletop game system.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
